Match Report 1: PSV Eindhoven

Season-Week: 2025-2026, Week 10

Opponent: Feyenoord 

Match Information:

Nominal Formation: 4-2-3-1

In Possession: 3-2-5 / CB-CB-LB or RB

Out of Possession: 5-2-3

Build-up:

Pressing: High press and high defensive line

Transitions: After regaining possession, PSV looked to attack quickly through vertical passes and direct runs. When possession was lost, they attempted to counter-press immediately.

Strengths: Forcing the opponent to defend, creating a chance for a quick counter-attack through high-tempo pressing when the opponent is attacking, and saving time in regaining possession of the ball.

Weaknesses: The risk of conceding counter-attacks is high; the full-backs' defensive skills aren't strong enough, and there's a high risk of being caught with too few players when the ball is lost.

